#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="an5.76"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an5.76:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 5 "
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 5 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an5.76:0.2"
msgid "8. Yodhājīvavagga "
msgstr "8. Warriors "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
#. VAR: dutiyayodhājīvūpamasuttaṃ (bj)
msgctxt "an5.76:0.3"
msgid "76. Dutiyayodhājīvasutta "
msgstr "76. Warriors (2nd) "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli3.94, sc1
msgctxt "an5.76:1.1"
msgid "“Pañcime, bhikkhave, yodhājīvā santo saṃvijjamānā lokasmiṃ. "
msgstr "“Mendicants, these five warriors are found in the world. "

msgctxt "an5.76:1.2"
msgid "Katame pañca? "
msgstr "What five? "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an5.76:1.3"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco yodhājīvo asicammaṃ gahetvā dhanukalāpaṃ sannayhitvā viyūḷhaṃ saṅgāmaṃ otarati. "
msgstr "Firstly, one warrior dons his sword and shield, fastens his bow and arrows, and plunges into the thick of battle. "

msgctxt "an5.76:1.4"
msgid "So tasmiṃ saṅgāme ussahati vāyamati. "
msgstr "He strives and struggles in the battle, "

msgctxt "an5.76:1.5"
msgid "Tamenaṃ ussahantaṃ vāyamantaṃ pare hananti pariyāpādenti. "
msgstr "but his foes kill him and finish him off. "

msgctxt "an5.76:1.6"
msgid "Evarūpopi, bhikkhave, idhekacco yodhājīvo hoti. "
msgstr "Some warriors are like that. "

msgctxt "an5.76:1.7"
msgid "Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, paṭhamo yodhājīvo santo saṃvijjamāno lokasmiṃ. "
msgstr "This is the first warrior found in the world. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "an5.76:2.1"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, idhekacco yodhājīvo asicammaṃ gahetvā dhanukalāpaṃ sannayhitvā viyūḷhaṃ saṅgāmaṃ otarati. "
msgstr "Furthermore, one warrior dons his sword and shield, fastens his bow and arrows, and plunges into the thick of battle. "

msgctxt "an5.76:2.2"
msgid "So tasmiṃ saṅgāme ussahati vāyamati. "
msgstr "He strives and struggles in the battle, "

#. VAR: upalikkhanti → upalikhanti (mr)
msgctxt "an5.76:2.3"
msgid "Tamenaṃ ussahantaṃ vāyamantaṃ pare upalikkhanti, tamenaṃ apanenti; "
msgstr "but his foes wound him. "

msgctxt "an5.76:2.4"
msgid "apanetvā ñātakānaṃ nenti. "
msgstr "He’s carried off and taken to his relatives, "

msgctxt "an5.76:2.5"
msgid "So ñātakehi nīyamāno appatvāva ñātake antarāmagge kālaṃ karoti. "
msgstr "but he dies on the road before he reaches them. "

msgctxt "an5.76:2.6"
msgid "Evarūpopi, bhikkhave, idhekacco yodhājīvo hoti. "
msgstr "Some warriors are like that. "

msgctxt "an5.76:2.7"
msgid "Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, dutiyo yodhājīvo santo saṃvijjamāno lokasmiṃ. "
msgstr "This is the second warrior found in the world. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "an5.76:3.1"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, idhekacco yodhājīvo asicammaṃ gahetvā dhanukalāpaṃ sannayhitvā viyūḷhaṃ saṅgāmaṃ otarati. "
msgstr "Furthermore, one warrior dons his sword and shield, fastens his bow and arrows, and plunges into the thick of battle. "

msgctxt "an5.76:3.2"
msgid "So tasmiṃ saṅgāme ussahati vāyamati. "
msgstr "He strives and struggles in the battle, "

msgctxt "an5.76:3.3"
msgid "Tamenaṃ ussahantaṃ vāyamantaṃ pare upalikkhanti, tamenaṃ apanenti; "
msgstr "but his foes wound him. "

msgctxt "an5.76:3.4"
msgid "apanetvā ñātakānaṃ nenti. "
msgstr "He’s carried off and taken to his relatives, "

msgctxt "an5.76:3.5"
msgid "Tamenaṃ ñātakā upaṭṭhahanti paricaranti. "
msgstr "who nurse him and care for him. "

msgctxt "an5.76:3.6"
msgid "So ñātakehi upaṭṭhahiyamāno paricariyamāno teneva ābādhena kālaṃ karoti. "
msgstr "But he dies of his injuries while in their care. "

msgctxt "an5.76:3.7"
msgid "Evarūpopi, bhikkhave, idhekacco yodhājīvo hoti. "
msgstr "Some warriors are like that. "

msgctxt "an5.76:3.8"
msgid "Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, tatiyo yodhājīvo santo saṃvijjamāno lokasmiṃ. "
msgstr "This is the third warrior found in the world. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc4
msgctxt "an5.76:4.1"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, idhekacco yodhājīvo asicammaṃ gahetvā dhanukalāpaṃ sannayhitvā viyūḷhaṃ saṅgāmaṃ otarati. "
msgstr "Furthermore, one warrior dons his sword and shield, fastens his bow and arrows, and plunges into the thick of battle. "

msgctxt "an5.76:4.2"
msgid "So tasmiṃ saṅgāme ussahati vāyamati. "
msgstr "He strives and struggles in the battle, "

msgctxt "an5.76:4.3"
msgid "Tamenaṃ ussahantaṃ vāyamantaṃ pare upalikkhanti, tamenaṃ apanenti; "
msgstr "but his foes wound him. "

msgctxt "an5.76:4.4"
msgid "apanetvā ñātakānaṃ nenti. "
msgstr "He’s carried off and taken to his relatives, "

msgctxt "an5.76:4.5"
msgid "Tamenaṃ ñātakā upaṭṭhahanti paricaranti. "
msgstr "who nurse him and care for him. "

msgctxt "an5.76:4.6"
msgid "So ñātakehi upaṭṭhahiyamāno paricariyamāno vuṭṭhāti tamhā ābādhā. "
msgstr "And while in their care, he recovers from his injuries. "

msgctxt "an5.76:4.7"
msgid "Evarūpopi, bhikkhave, idhekacco yodhājīvo hoti. "
msgstr "Some warriors are like that. "

msgctxt "an5.76:4.8"
msgid "Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, catuttho yodhājīvo santo saṃvijjamāno lokasmiṃ. "
msgstr "This is the fourth warrior found in the world. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli3.95, sc5
msgctxt "an5.76:5.1"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, idhekacco yodhājīvo asicammaṃ gahetvā dhanukalāpaṃ sannayhitvā viyūḷhaṃ saṅgāmaṃ otarati. "
msgstr "Furthermore, one warrior dons his sword and shield, fastens his bow and arrows, and plunges into the thick of battle. "

msgctxt "an5.76:5.2"
msgid "So taṃ saṅgāmaṃ abhivijinitvā vijitasaṅgāmo tameva saṅgāmasīsaṃ ajjhāvasati. "
msgstr "He wins victory in battle, establishing himself as foremost in battle. "

msgctxt "an5.76:5.3"
msgid "Evarūpopi, bhikkhave, idhekacco yodhājīvo hoti. "
msgstr "Some warriors are like that. "

msgctxt "an5.76:5.4"
msgid "Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, pañcamo yodhājīvo santo saṃvijjamāno lokasmiṃ. "
msgstr "This is the fifth warrior found in the world. "

msgctxt "an5.76:5.5"
msgid "Ime kho, bhikkhave, pañca yodhājīvā santo saṃvijjamānā lokasmiṃ. "
msgstr "These are the five warriors found in the world. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc6
#. VAR: pañcime → pañca (bj)
msgctxt "an5.76:6.1"
msgid "Evamevaṃ kho, bhikkhave, pañcime yodhājīvūpamā puggalā santo saṃvijjamānā bhikkhūsu. "
msgstr "In the same way, these five people similar to warriors are found among the monks. "

msgctxt "an5.76:6.2"
msgid "Katame pañca? "
msgstr "What five? "

msgctxt "an5.76:6.3"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu aññataraṃ gāmaṃ vā nigamaṃ vā upanissāya viharati. "
msgstr "Firstly, a mendicant lives supported by a town or village. "

msgctxt "an5.76:6.4"
msgid "So pubbaṇhasamayaṃ nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya tameva gāmaṃ vā nigamaṃ vā piṇḍāya pavisati arakkhiteneva kāyena arakkhitāya vācāya arakkhitena cittena anupaṭṭhitāya satiyā asaṃvutehi indriyehi. "
msgstr "He robes up in the morning and, taking his bowl and robe, enters a village or town for alms without guarding body, speech, and mind, without establishing mindfulness, and without restraining the sense faculties. "

msgctxt "an5.76:6.5"
msgid "So tattha passati mātugāmaṃ dunnivatthaṃ vā duppārutaṃ vā. "
msgstr "There he sees a female scantily clad, with revealing clothes. "

msgctxt "an5.76:6.6"
msgid "Tassa taṃ mātugāmaṃ disvā dunnivatthaṃ vā duppārutaṃ vā rāgo cittaṃ anuddhaṃseti. "
msgstr "Lust infects his mind, "

msgctxt "an5.76:6.7"
msgid "So rāgānuddhaṃsitena cittena sikkhaṃ apaccakkhāya dubbalyaṃ anāvikatvā methunaṃ dhammaṃ paṭisevati. "
msgstr "and, without rejecting the training and declaring his inability to continue, he has sex. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc7
msgctxt "an5.76:7.1"
msgid "Seyyathāpi so, bhikkhave, yodhājīvo asicammaṃ gahetvā dhanukalāpaṃ sannayhitvā viyūḷhaṃ saṅgāmaṃ otarati, so tasmiṃ saṅgāme ussahati vāyamati, tamenaṃ ussahantaṃ vāyamantaṃ pare hananti pariyāpādenti; tathūpamāhaṃ, bhikkhave, imaṃ puggalaṃ vadāmi. Evarūpopi, bhikkhave, idhekacco puggalo hoti. "
msgstr "I say that this person is like the warrior who is killed and finished off by his foes. Some people are like that. "

msgctxt "an5.76:7.2"
msgid "Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, paṭhamo yodhājīvūpamo puggalo santo saṃvijjamāno bhikkhūsu. "
msgstr "This is the first person similar to a warrior found among the monks. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli3.96, sc8
msgctxt "an5.76:8.1"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhu aññataraṃ gāmaṃ vā nigamaṃ vā upanissāya viharati. "
msgstr "Furthermore, a mendicant lives supported by a town or village. "

msgctxt "an5.76:8.2"
msgid "So pubbaṇhasamayaṃ nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya tameva gāmaṃ vā nigamaṃ vā piṇḍāya pavisati arakkhiteneva kāyena arakkhitāya vācāya arakkhitena cittena anupaṭṭhitāya satiyā asaṃvutehi indriyehi. "
msgstr "He robes up in the morning and, taking his bowl and robe, enters a village or town for alms without guarding body, speech, and mind, without establishing mindfulness, and without restraining the sense faculties. "

msgctxt "an5.76:8.3"
msgid "So tattha passati mātugāmaṃ dunnivatthaṃ vā duppārutaṃ vā. "
msgstr "There he sees a female scantily clad, with revealing clothes. "

msgctxt "an5.76:8.4"
msgid "Tassa taṃ mātugāmaṃ disvā dunnivatthaṃ vā duppārutaṃ vā rāgo cittaṃ anuddhaṃseti. "
msgstr "Lust infects his mind, "

msgctxt "an5.76:8.5"
msgid "So rāgānuddhaṃsitena cittena pariḍayhateva kāyena pariḍayhati cetasā. "
msgstr "and his body and mind burn with it. "

msgctxt "an5.76:8.6"
msgid "Tassa evaṃ hoti: "
msgstr "He thinks: "

msgctxt "an5.76:8.7"
msgid "‘yannūnāhaṃ ārāmaṃ gantvā bhikkhūnaṃ āroceyyaṃ—"
msgstr "‘Why don’t I go to the monastery and tell the monks: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. VAR: rāgapariyuṭṭhitomhi → rāgāyitomhi (bj, s1-3, km)
#. VAR: sandhāretuṃ → santānetuṃ (bj, s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "an5.76:8.8"
msgid "rāgapariyuṭṭhitomhi, āvuso, rāgapareto, na sakkomi brahmacariyaṃ sandhāretuṃ; "
msgstr "“Reverends, I am overcome with lust, mired in lust. I am unable to keep up the spiritual life. "

msgctxt "an5.76:8.9"
msgid "sikkhādubbalyaṃ āvikatvā sikkhaṃ paccakkhāya hīnāyāvattissāmī’ti. "
msgstr "I declare my inability to continue training. I reject it and will return to a lesser life.”’ "

msgctxt "an5.76:8.10"
msgid "So ārāmaṃ gacchanto appatvāva ārāmaṃ antarāmagge sikkhādubbalyaṃ āvikatvā sikkhaṃ paccakkhāya hīnāyāvattati. "
msgstr "But while traveling on the road, before he reaches the monastery he declares his inability to continue training. He rejects it and returns to a lesser life. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc9
msgctxt "an5.76:9.1"
msgid "Seyyathāpi so, bhikkhave, yodhājīvo asicammaṃ gahetvā dhanukalāpaṃ sannayhitvā viyūḷhaṃ saṅgāmaṃ otarati, so tasmiṃ saṅgāme ussahati vāyamati, tamenaṃ ussahantaṃ vāyamantaṃ pare upalikkhanti, tamenaṃ apanenti; apanetvā ñātakānaṃ nenti. So ñātakehi nīyamāno appatvāva ñātake antarāmagge kālaṃ karoti; tathūpamāhaṃ, bhikkhave, imaṃ puggalaṃ vadāmi. Evarūpopi, bhikkhave, idhekacco puggalo hoti. "
msgstr "I say that this person is like the warrior who is taken to his relatives for care, but he dies on the road before he reaches them. Some people are like that. "

msgctxt "an5.76:9.2"
msgid "Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, dutiyo yodhājīvūpamo puggalo santo saṃvijjamāno bhikkhūsu. "
msgstr "This is the second person similar to a warrior found among the monks. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc10
msgctxt "an5.76:10.1"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhu aññataraṃ gāmaṃ vā nigamaṃ vā upanissāya viharati. "
msgstr "Furthermore, a mendicant lives supported by a town or village. "

msgctxt "an5.76:10.2"
msgid "So pubbaṇhasamayaṃ nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya tameva gāmaṃ vā nigamaṃ vā piṇḍāya pavisati arakkhiteneva kāyena arakkhitāya vācāya arakkhitena cittena anupaṭṭhitāya satiyā asaṃvutehi indriyehi. "
msgstr "He robes up in the morning and, taking his bowl and robe, enters a village or town for alms without guarding body, speech, and mind, without establishing mindfulness, and without restraining the sense faculties. "

msgctxt "an5.76:10.3"
msgid "So tattha passati mātugāmaṃ dunnivatthaṃ vā duppārutaṃ vā. "
msgstr "There he sees a female scantily clad, with revealing clothes. "

msgctxt "an5.76:10.4"
msgid "Tassa taṃ mātugāmaṃ disvā dunnivatthaṃ vā duppārutaṃ vā rāgo cittaṃ anuddhaṃseti. "
msgstr "Lust infects his mind, "

msgctxt "an5.76:10.5"
msgid "So rāgānuddhaṃsitena cittena pariḍayhateva kāyena pariḍayhati cetasā. "
msgstr "and his body and mind burn with it. "

msgctxt "an5.76:10.6"
msgid "Tassa evaṃ hoti: "
msgstr "He thinks: "

msgctxt "an5.76:10.7"
msgid "‘yannūnāhaṃ ārāmaṃ gantvā bhikkhūnaṃ āroceyyaṃ—"
msgstr "‘Why don’t I go to the monastery and tell the monks: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an5.76:10.8"
msgid "rāgapariyuṭṭhitomhi, āvuso, rāgapareto, na sakkomi brahmacariyaṃ sandhāretuṃ; "
msgstr "“Reverends, I am overcome with lust, mired in lust. I am unable to keep up the spiritual life. "

msgctxt "an5.76:10.9"
msgid "sikkhādubbalyaṃ āvikatvā sikkhaṃ paccakkhāya hīnāyāvattissāmī’ti. "
msgstr "I declare my inability to continue training. I reject it and will return to a lesser life.”’ "

msgctxt "an5.76:10.10"
msgid "So ārāmaṃ gantvā bhikkhūnaṃ āroceti: "
msgstr "He goes to the monastery and tells the monks: "

msgctxt "an5.76:10.11"
msgid "‘rāgapariyuṭṭhitomhi, āvuso, rāgapareto, na sakkomi brahmacariyaṃ sandhāretuṃ; "
msgstr "‘Reverends, I am overcome with lust, mired in lust. I am unable to keep up the spiritual life. "

msgctxt "an5.76:10.12"
msgid "sikkhādubbalyaṃ āvikatvā sikkhaṃ paccakkhāya hīnāyāvattissāmī’ti. "
msgstr "I declare my inability to continue training. I reject it and will return to a lesser life.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli3.97, sc11
msgctxt "an5.76:11.1"
msgid "Tamenaṃ sabrahmacārī ovadanti anusāsanti: "
msgstr "His spiritual companions advise and instruct him: "

#. VAR: bahupāyāsā → bahūpāyāsā (bj, s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "an5.76:11.2"
msgid "‘appassādā, āvuso, kāmā vuttā bhagavatā bahudukkhā bahupāyāsā, ādīnavo ettha bhiyyo. "
msgstr "‘Reverend, the Buddha says that sensual pleasures give little gratification and much suffering and distress, and they are all the more full of drawbacks. "

msgctxt "an5.76:11.3"
msgid "Aṭṭhikaṅkalūpamā kāmā vuttā bhagavatā bahudukkhā bahupāyāsā, ādīnavo ettha bhiyyo. "
msgstr "With the similes of a skeleton … "

msgctxt "an5.76:11.4"
msgid "Maṃsapesūpamā kāmā vuttā bhagavatā bahudukkhā bahupāyāsā, ādīnavo ettha bhiyyo. "
msgstr "a lump of meat … "

msgctxt "an5.76:11.5"
msgid "Tiṇukkūpamā kāmā vuttā bhagavatā bahudukkhā bahupāyāsā, ādīnavo ettha bhiyyo. "
msgstr "a grass torch … "

msgctxt "an5.76:11.6"
msgid "Aṅgārakāsūpamā kāmā vuttā bhagavatā bahudukkhā bahupāyāsā, ādīnavo ettha bhiyyo. "
msgstr "a pit of glowing coals … "

msgctxt "an5.76:11.7"
msgid "Supinakūpamā kāmā vuttā bhagavatā bahudukkhā bahupāyāsā, ādīnavo ettha bhiyyo. "
msgstr "a dream … "

msgctxt "an5.76:11.8"
msgid "Yācitakūpamā kāmā vuttā bhagavatā bahudukkhā bahupāyāsā, ādīnavo ettha bhiyyo. "
msgstr "borrowed goods … "

msgctxt "an5.76:11.9"
msgid "Rukkhaphalūpamā kāmā vuttā bhagavatā bahudukkhā bahupāyāsā, ādīnavo ettha bhiyyo. "
msgstr "fruit on a tree … "

msgctxt "an5.76:11.10"
msgid "Asisūnūpamā kāmā vuttā bhagavatā bahudukkhā bahupāyāsā, ādīnavo ettha bhiyyo. "
msgstr "a butcher’s knife and chopping block … "

msgctxt "an5.76:11.11"
msgid "Sattisūlūpamā kāmā vuttā bhagavatā bahudukkhā bahupāyāsā, ādīnavo ettha bhiyyo. "
msgstr "a staking sword … "

msgctxt "an5.76:11.12"
msgid "Sappasirūpamā kāmā vuttā bhagavatā bahudukkhā bahupāyāsā, ādīnavo ettha bhiyyo. "
msgstr "a snake’s head, the Buddha says that sensual pleasures give little gratification and much suffering and distress, and they are all the more full of drawbacks. "

msgctxt "an5.76:11.13"
msgid "Abhiramatāyasmā brahmacariye; "
msgstr "Be happy with the spiritual life. "

# NOTE: I don’t know why BB has “think” here, the text as always has avikatva (declare). Also note the use of “venerable”, as contrasted with “avuso” earlier.
msgctxt "an5.76:11.14"
msgid "māyasmā sikkhādubbalyaṃ āvikatvā sikkhaṃ paccakkhāya hīnāyāvattī’ti. "
msgstr "Venerable, please don’t declare your inability to continue training, reject it and return to a lesser life.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc12
msgctxt "an5.76:12.1"
msgid "So sabrahmacārīhi evaṃ ovadiyamāno evaṃ anusāsiyamāno evamāha: "
msgstr "When thus advised and instructed by his spiritual companions, he says: "

msgctxt "an5.76:12.2"
msgid "‘kiñcāpi, āvuso, appassādā kāmā vuttā bhagavatā bahudukkhā bahupāyāsā, ādīnavo ettha bhiyyo; "
msgstr "‘Reverends, even though the Buddha says that sensual pleasures give little gratification and much suffering and distress, and they are all the more full of drawbacks, "

msgctxt "an5.76:12.3"
msgid "atha kho nevāhaṃ sakkomi brahmacariyaṃ sandhāretuṃ, sikkhādubbalyaṃ āvikatvā sikkhaṃ paccakkhāya hīnāyāvattissāmī’ti. "
msgstr "I am unable to keep up the spiritual life. I declare my inability to continue training. I reject it and will return to a lesser life.’ "

msgctxt "an5.76:12.4"
msgid "So sikkhādubbalyaṃ āvikatvā sikkhaṃ paccakkhāya hīnāyāvattati. "
msgstr "Declaring his inability to continue training, he rejects it and returns to a lesser life. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli3.98, sc13
msgctxt "an5.76:13.1"
msgid "Seyyathāpi so, bhikkhave, yodhājīvo asicammaṃ gahetvā dhanukalāpaṃ sannayhitvā viyūḷhaṃ saṅgāmaṃ otarati, so tasmiṃ saṅgāme ussahati vāyamati, tamenaṃ ussahantaṃ vāyamantaṃ pare upalikkhanti, tamenaṃ apanenti; apanetvā ñātakānaṃ nenti, tamenaṃ ñātakā upaṭṭhahanti paricaranti. So ñātakehi upaṭṭhahiyamāno paricariyamāno teneva ābādhena kālaṃ karoti; tathūpamāhaṃ, bhikkhave, imaṃ puggalaṃ vadāmi. Evarūpopi, bhikkhave, idhekacco puggalo hoti. "
msgstr "I say that this person is like the warrior who dies of his injuries while in the care of his relatives. Some people are like that. "

msgctxt "an5.76:13.2"
msgid "Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, tatiyo yodhājīvūpamo puggalo santo saṃvijjamāno bhikkhūsu. "
msgstr "This is the third person similar to a warrior found among the monks. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc14
msgctxt "an5.76:14.1"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhu aññataraṃ gāmaṃ vā nigamaṃ vā upanissāya viharati. "
msgstr "Furthermore, a mendicant lives supported by a town or village. "

msgctxt "an5.76:14.2"
msgid "So pubbaṇhasamayaṃ nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya tameva gāmaṃ vā nigamaṃ vā piṇḍāya pavisati arakkhiteneva kāyena arakkhitāya vācāya arakkhitena cittena anupaṭṭhitāya satiyā asaṃvutehi indriyehi. "
msgstr "He robes up in the morning and, taking his bowl and robe, enters a village or town for alms without guarding body, speech, and mind, without establishing mindfulness, and without restraining the sense faculties. "

msgctxt "an5.76:14.3"
msgid "So tattha passati mātugāmaṃ dunnivatthaṃ vā duppārutaṃ vā. "
msgstr "There he sees a female scantily clad, with revealing clothes. "

msgctxt "an5.76:14.4"
msgid "Tassa taṃ mātugāmaṃ disvā dunnivatthaṃ vā duppārutaṃ vā rāgo cittaṃ anuddhaṃseti. "
msgstr "Lust infects his mind, "

msgctxt "an5.76:14.5"
msgid "So rāgānuddhaṃsitena cittena pariḍayhateva kāyena pariḍayhati cetasā. "
msgstr "and his body and mind burn with it. "

msgctxt "an5.76:14.6"
msgid "Tassa evaṃ hoti: "
msgstr "He thinks: "

msgctxt "an5.76:14.7"
msgid "‘yannūnāhaṃ ārāmaṃ gantvā bhikkhūnaṃ āroceyyaṃ—"
msgstr "‘Why don’t I go to the monastery and tell the monks: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an5.76:14.8"
msgid "rāgapariyuṭṭhitomhi, āvuso, rāgapareto, na sakkomi brahmacariyaṃ sandhāretuṃ; "
msgstr "“Reverends, I am overcome with lust, mired in lust. I am unable to keep up the spiritual life. "

msgctxt "an5.76:14.9"
msgid "sikkhādubbalyaṃ āvikatvā sikkhaṃ paccakkhāya hīnāyāvattissāmī’ti. "
msgstr "I declare my inability to continue training. I reject it and will return to a lesser life.”’ "

msgctxt "an5.76:14.10"
msgid "So ārāmaṃ gantvā bhikkhūnaṃ āroceti: "
msgstr "He goes to the monastery and tells the monks: "

msgctxt "an5.76:14.11"
msgid "‘rāgapariyuṭṭhitomhi, āvuso, rāgapareto, na sakkomi brahmacariyaṃ sandhāretuṃ; "
msgstr "‘Reverends, I am overcome with lust, mired in lust. I am unable to keep up the spiritual life. "

msgctxt "an5.76:14.12"
msgid "sikkhādubbalyaṃ āvikatvā sikkhaṃ paccakkhāya hīnāyāvattissāmī’ti. "
msgstr "I declare my inability to continue training. I reject it and will return to a lesser life.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli3.99, sc15
msgctxt "an5.76:15.1"
msgid "Tamenaṃ sabrahmacārī ovadanti anusāsanti: "
msgstr "His spiritual companions advise and instruct him: "

msgctxt "an5.76:15.2"
msgid "‘appassādā, āvuso, kāmā vuttā bhagavatā bahudukkhā bahupāyāsā, ādīnavo ettha bhiyyo. "
msgstr "‘Reverend, the Buddha says that sensual pleasures give little gratification and much suffering and distress, and they are all the more full of drawbacks. "

msgctxt "an5.76:15.3"
msgid "Aṭṭhikaṅkalūpamā kāmā vuttā bhagavatā bahudukkhā bahupāyāsā, ādīnavo ettha bhiyyo. "
msgstr "With the simile of a skeleton … "

msgctxt "an5.76:15.4"
msgid "Maṃsapesūpamā kāmā vuttā bhagavatā … pe … tiṇukkūpamā kāmā vuttā bhagavatā … aṅgārakāsūpamā kāmā vuttā bhagavatā … supinakūpamā kāmā vuttā bhagavatā … yācitakūpamā kāmā vuttā bhagavatā … rukkhaphalūpamā kāmā vuttā bhagavatā … asisūnūpamā kāmā vuttā bhagavatā … sattisūlūpamā kāmā vuttā bhagavatā … sappasirūpamā kāmā vuttā bhagavatā bahudukkhā bahupāyāsā, ādīnavo ettha bhiyyo. "
msgstr "a lump of meat … a grass torch … a pit of glowing coals … a dream … borrowed goods … fruit on a tree … a butcher’s knife and chopping block … a staking sword … a snake’s head, the Buddha says that sensual pleasures give little gratification and much suffering and distress, and they are all the more full of drawbacks. "

msgctxt "an5.76:15.5"
msgid "Abhiramatāyasmā brahmacariye; "
msgstr "Be happy with the spiritual life. "

msgctxt "an5.76:15.6"
msgid "māyasmā sikkhādubbalyaṃ āvikatvā sikkhaṃ paccakkhāya hīnāyāvattī’ti. "
msgstr "Venerable, please don’t declare your inability to continue training, reject it and return to a lesser life.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc16
msgctxt "an5.76:16.1"
msgid "So sabrahmacārīhi evaṃ ovadiyamāno evaṃ anusāsiyamāno evamāha: "
msgstr "When thus advised and instructed by his spiritual companions, he says: "

msgctxt "an5.76:16.2"
msgid "‘ussahissāmi, āvuso, vāyamissāmi, āvuso, abhiramissāmi, āvuso. "
msgstr "‘I’ll try, reverends, I’ll struggle, I’ll be happy. "

msgctxt "an5.76:16.3"
msgid "Na dānāhaṃ, āvuso, sikkhādubbalyaṃ āvikatvā sikkhaṃ paccakkhāya hīnāyāvattissāmī’ti. "
msgstr "I won’t now declare my inability to continue training, reject it and return to a lesser life.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc17
msgctxt "an5.76:17.1"
msgid "Seyyathāpi so, bhikkhave, yodhājīvo asicammaṃ gahetvā dhanukalāpaṃ sannayhitvā viyūḷhaṃ saṅgāmaṃ otarati, so tasmiṃ saṅgāme ussahati vāyamati, tamenaṃ ussahantaṃ vāyamantaṃ pare upalikkhanti, tamenaṃ apanenti; apanetvā ñātakānaṃ nenti, tamenaṃ ñātakā upaṭṭhahanti paricaranti. So ñātakehi upaṭṭhahiyamāno paricariyamāno vuṭṭhāti tamhā ābādhā; tathūpamāhaṃ, bhikkhave, imaṃ puggalaṃ vadāmi. "
msgstr "I say that this person is like the warrior who recovers from his injuries while in the care of his relatives. "

msgctxt "an5.76:17.2"
msgid "Evarūpopi, bhikkhave, idhekacco puggalo hoti. "
msgstr "Some people are like that. "

msgctxt "an5.76:17.3"
msgid "Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, catuttho yodhājīvūpamo puggalo santo saṃvijjamāno bhikkhūsu. "
msgstr "This is the fourth person similar to a warrior found among the monks. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli3.100, sc18
msgctxt "an5.76:18.1"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhu aññataraṃ gāmaṃ vā nigamaṃ vā upanissāya viharati. "
msgstr "Furthermore, a mendicant lives supported by a town or village. "

msgctxt "an5.76:18.2"
msgid "So pubbaṇhasamayaṃ nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya tameva gāmaṃ vā nigamaṃ vā piṇḍāya pavisati rakkhiteneva kāyena rakkhitāya vācāya rakkhitena cittena upaṭṭhitāya satiyā saṃvutehi indriyehi. "
msgstr "He robes up in the morning and, taking his bowl and robe, enters a village or town, guarding body, speech, and mind, establishing mindfulness, and restraining the sense faculties. "

msgctxt "an5.76:18.3"
msgid "So cakkhunā rūpaṃ disvā na nimittaggāhī hoti nānubyañjanaggāhī. "
msgstr "Seeing a sight with his eyes, he doesn’t get caught up in the features and details. "

msgctxt "an5.76:18.4"
msgid "Yatvādhikaraṇamenaṃ cakkhundriyaṃ asaṃvutaṃ viharantaṃ abhijjhādomanassā pāpakā akusalā dhammā anvāssaveyyuṃ, tassa saṃvarāya paṭipajjati; rakkhati cakkhundriyaṃ; cakkhundriye saṃvaraṃ āpajjati. "
msgstr "If the faculty of sight were left unrestrained, bad unskillful qualities of desire and aversion would become overwhelming. For this reason, he practices restraint, protecting the faculty of sight, and achieving restraint over it. "

msgctxt "an5.76:18.5"
msgid "Sotena saddaṃ sutvā … "
msgstr "Hearing a sound with his ears … "

msgctxt "an5.76:18.6"
msgid "ghānena gandhaṃ ghāyitvā … "
msgstr "Smelling an odor with his nose … "

msgctxt "an5.76:18.7"
msgid "jivhāya rasaṃ sāyitvā … "
msgstr "Tasting a flavor with his tongue … "

msgctxt "an5.76:18.8"
msgid "kāyena phoṭṭhabbaṃ phusitvā … "
msgstr "Feeling a touch with his body … "

msgctxt "an5.76:18.9"
msgid "manasā dhammaṃ viññāya na nimittaggāhī hoti nānubyañjanaggāhī. "
msgstr "Knowing a thought with his mind, he doesn’t get caught up in the features and details. "

msgctxt "an5.76:18.10"
msgid "Yatvādhikaraṇamenaṃ manindriyaṃ asaṃvutaṃ viharantaṃ abhijjhādomanassā pāpakā akusalā dhammā anvāssaveyyuṃ, tassa saṃvarāya paṭipajjati; rakkhati manindriyaṃ; manindriye saṃvaraṃ āpajjati. "
msgstr "If the faculty of mind were left unrestrained, bad unskillful qualities of desire and aversion would become overwhelming. For this reason, he practices restraint, protecting the faculty of mind, and achieving restraint over it. "

msgctxt "an5.76:18.11"
msgid "So pacchābhattaṃ piṇḍapātapaṭikkanto "
msgstr "Then after the meal, on his return from alms-round, "

msgctxt "an5.76:18.12"
msgid "vivittaṃ senāsanaṃ bhajati araññaṃ rukkhamūlaṃ pabbataṃ kandaraṃ giriguhaṃ susānaṃ vanapatthaṃ abbhokāsaṃ palālapuñjaṃ. "
msgstr "he frequents a secluded lodging—a wilderness, the root of a tree, a hill, a ravine, a mountain cave, a charnel ground, a forest, the open air, a heap of straw. "

msgctxt "an5.76:18.13"
msgid "So araññagato vā rukkhamūlagato vā suññāgāragato vā nisīdati pallaṅkaṃ ābhujitvā ujuṃ kāyaṃ paṇidhāya parimukhaṃ satiṃ upaṭṭhapetvā. "
msgstr "Gone to a wilderness, or to the root of a tree, or to an empty hut, he sits down cross-legged, with his body straight, and establishes mindfulness right there. "

msgctxt "an5.76:18.14"
msgid "So abhijjhaṃ loke pahāya … pe … so ime pañca nīvaraṇe pahāya cetaso upakkilese paññāya dubbalīkaraṇe "
msgstr "He gives up these five hindrances, corruptions of the heart that weaken wisdom. "

msgctxt "an5.76:18.15"
msgid "vivicceva kāmehi … pe … catutthaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati. "
msgstr "Then, quite secluded from sensual pleasures, secluded from unskillful qualities, he enters and remains in the first absorption … second absorption … third absorption … fourth absorption. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc19
msgctxt "an5.76:19.1"
msgid "So evaṃ samāhite citte parisuddhe pariyodāte anaṅgaṇe vigatūpakkilese mudubhūte kammaniye ṭhite āneñjappatte āsavānaṃ khayañāṇāya cittaṃ abhininnāmeti. "
msgstr "When his mind has become immersed in samādhi like this—purified, bright, flawless, rid of corruptions, pliable, workable, steady, and imperturbable—he extends it toward knowledge of the ending of defilements. "

msgctxt "an5.76:19.2"
msgid "So ‘idaṃ dukkhan’ti yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti … pe … nāparaṃ itthattāyāti pajānāti. "
msgstr "He truly understands: ‘This is suffering’ … ‘This is the origin of suffering’ … ‘This is the cessation of suffering’ … ‘This is the practice that leads to the cessation of suffering’. He truly understands: ‘These are defilements’ … ‘This is the origin of defilements’ … ‘This is the cessation of defilements’ … ‘This is the practice that leads to the cessation of defilements’. Knowing and seeing like this, his mind is freed from the defilements of sensuality, desire to be reborn, and ignorance. When freed, he knows ‘it is freed’. He understands: ‘Rebirth is ended, the spiritual journey has been completed, what had to be done has been done, there is no return to any state of existence.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc20
msgctxt "an5.76:20.1"
msgid "Seyyathāpi so, bhikkhave, yodhājīvo asicammaṃ gahetvā dhanukalāpaṃ sannayhitvā viyūḷhaṃ saṅgāmaṃ otarati, so taṃ saṅgāmaṃ abhivijinitvā vijitasaṅgāmo tameva saṅgāmasīsaṃ ajjhāvasati; tathūpamāhaṃ, bhikkhave, imaṃ puggalaṃ vadāmi. "
msgstr "I say that this person is like the warrior who dons his sword and shield, fastens his bow and arrows, and plunges into the thick of battle. He wins victory in battle, establishing himself as foremost in battle. "

msgctxt "an5.76:20.2"
msgid "Evarūpopi, bhikkhave, idhekacco puggalo hoti. "
msgstr "Some people are like that. "

msgctxt "an5.76:20.3"
msgid "Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, pañcamo yodhājīvūpamo puggalo santo saṃvijjamāno bhikkhūsu. "
msgstr "This is the fifth person similar to a warrior found among the monks. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an5.76:20.4"
msgid "Ime kho, bhikkhave, pañca yodhājīvūpamā puggalā santo saṃvijjamānā bhikkhūsū”ti. "
msgstr "These five people similar to warriors are found among the monks.” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an5.76:20.5"
msgid "Chaṭṭhaṃ. "
msgstr ""

